    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "The most common asphalt-shingle install nationally is a gray in this exact tonal zone. Cliffside sits right inside that fairway: dark enough to feel anchored, light enough to keep the elevation breathing. The granule blend is engineered to read as a single quiet plane from the street.",
      "GAF uses a tight blend of dark gray and faint blue-gray granules to keep the surface visually alive. The result is a roof that reads as a clean architectural line from the street and a textured surface up close.",
      "A safe specification if you have not committed to a final paint color yet. It cools the rest of the elevation visually and makes warm accents (cedar, stone, copper) look richer."
    ],
